PREHEAT oven to 375 degrees F. PLACE bell peppers in microwave-safe dish with 3 tablespoons water. Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on HIGH (100%) power for 4 to 5 minutes or until slightly tender. Drain. COMBINE rice, peas and carrots, corn, green onions, 3/4 cup salsa and 1 cup cheese in large bowl. Fill each pepper with about 1/2 cup rice mixture. Place peppers in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; top with remaining salsa and remaining cheese. BAKE, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes. Uncover; bake for additional 5 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.